as &ldquo;Conference Hall&rdquo; at the locality mentioned i.e. Babutlang. The following four centres are located at Babutlang which could possibly be used for such seminars, which are as follows:-</p> <p style="text-align:justify"></p> Archive Hall Engineers Club YMA Conference Hall Co-operative Conference Hall <p style="text-align:justify"></p> <p style="text-align:justify">Contacting the authorities of the above said 4 halls revealed that none of them had been hired on the date cited in the Writ Petition i.e. 13.12.09 not to mention the alleged interference by the Police. Further mentioned be made that business seminar/promotional meeting are hardly conducted on Sundays if not at all, which was the day on which 13.12.09 falls, as Mizoram is a Christian State. Therefore, the question arising is whether the claimed seminar was in fact really conducted by the petitioner or not, rather than the allegation that Mizoram Police interfere with it.</p> <p style="text-align:justify"></p> <p style="text-align:justify">4. SI No. 5 Para-III  Nagaland Police to comment</p> <p style="text-align:justify">5. SI No. 5 Para-IV  Assam Police to comment</p> <p style="text-align:justify"></p> <p style="text-align:justify"></p> <p style="text-align:justify"></p> <p style="text-align:justify"></p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left"></p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left"></p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left">Superintendent of Police</p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left"></p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left"></p> <p style="margin-left:360px; text-align:left"></p> </p>)'
